    question: "How much does basement waterproofing cost in Pickering?",
    answer: "Exterior waterproofing in Pickering costs $140-$275 per linear foot, with typical projects ranging from $12,000-$27,000 depending on foundation depth, proximity to lake/rivers, and conservation area requirements. Bay Ridges lakefront homes often need more robust systems ($17,000-$28,000) due to constant groundwater pressure. Newer subdivision homes in Duffin Heights typically cost less ($12,000-$20,000). Conservation area properties may have slightly higher costs due to TRCA compliance requirements. Interior drainage systems run $80-$200 per linear foot."
